WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:15.032 --> 00:00:17.392
<i>Record temperatures
in the New York area

3
00:00:17.450 --> 00:00:22.497
<i>as 100-degree weather hits its fifth
consecutive day with no end in sight.

4
00:00:22.580 --> 00:00:25.083
I'll tell you who I want!

5
00:00:27.335 --> 00:00:30.130
I told you I'll call you later.

6
00:00:31.214 --> 00:00:33.654
Yeah. you'll get what you want.

7
00:00:36.178 --> 00:00:38.138
...lowlife pulls a piece on me.

8
00:00:38.221 --> 00:00:39.306
It never worked!

9
00:00:39.389 --> 00:00:41.558
What's wrong with you?
I tell you not to touch...

10
00:00:46.646 --> 00:00:48.773
You want to move your car? Huh?

11
00:01:03.705 --> 00:01:05.748
Get out of the way!

12
00:01:08.543 --> 00:01:09.837
Oh. my God!

13
00:01:09.920 --> 00:01:11.338
Move. move!

14
00:01:17.177 --> 00:01:19.497
They opened fire.

15
00:01:21.098 --> 00:01:22.640
Move the hell out of the way!

16
00:01:28.563 --> 00:01:29.689
Drop the gun!

17
00:01:30.732 --> 00:01:32.817
Drop the gun and get on the ground...

18
00:02:00.178 --> 00:02:02.097
Out of my way!

19
00:02:02.180 --> 00:02:03.849
Move!

20
00:02:23.911 --> 00:02:26.788
Move. move. move!

21
00:02:26.872 --> 00:02:28.248
You get out of the car!

22
00:02:28.331 --> 00:02:30.417
- Get out of the way. now!
- Get out of the car. now!

23
00:02:32.544 --> 00:02:33.836
Call 911.

24
00:02:38.967 --> 00:02:41.303
- And then he went to...
- You! You!

25
00:02:43.180 --> 00:02:44.973
Stay calm!

26
00:02:45.473 --> 00:02:46.641
Call the cops.

27
00:02:46.724 --> 00:02:48.851
Let me go!
Please put me down.

28
00:02:52.647 --> 00:02:57.527
- Help! Anybody. please help!
- Shut up! Shut up!

29
00:03:47.452 --> 00:03:49.871
Stand back. everybody.
Okay. please. please.

30
00:05:23.548 --> 00:05:25.800
You ever wake up
in the morning...

31
00:05:25.883 --> 00:05:28.095
from the second you get out of bed.
it's like...

32
00:05:28.178 --> 00:05:29.929
every molecule in your body hurts?

33
00:05:30.012 --> 00:05:32.390
- No. never.
- I'm in agony. dude.

34
00:05:32.474 --> 00:05:33.600
What. did you go back to the gym?

35
00:05:33.683 --> 00:05:37.061
Hell. no. Do I look capable
of making healthy life choices?

36
00:05:37.145 --> 00:05:39.314
I went out. Matthew.
Went out dancing.

37
00:05:39.397 --> 00:05:41.899
- I'm choosing not to believe that.
- And yet. it's true.

38
00:05:41.983 --> 00:05:43.776
- Mind if I ask you a personal question?
- Go ahead.

39
00:05:43.860 --> 00:05:46.154
- Are you insane?
- Yes.

40
00:05:46.238 --> 00:05:49.366
- Tell me it was the barista.
- Hey. Foggy. Looking good!

41
00:05:50.283 --> 00:05:51.576
Her name is Bethany

42
00:05:51.659 --> 00:05:53.203
- and she is very limber.
- Oh!

43
00:05:53.286 --> 00:05:54.329
You're my hero.

44
00:05:55.622 --> 00:05:58.833
- Watch it. asshole.
- So. uh. when's the next date?

45
00:05:58.916 --> 00:06:01.002
- Well. therein lies the true pain.
- No!

46
00:06:01.085 --> 00:06:03.463
Yes. One and done.

47
00:06:03.546 --> 00:06:06.466
End of the night. she hugged me
like a cousin and said. "I'll call you."

48
00:06:06.549 --> 00:06:08.593
Oh. that's brutal.

49
00:06:08.676 --> 00:06:11.513
- You know what my problem is?
- Well. it ain't the moves.

50
00:06:11.596 --> 00:06:13.140
You know I got the moves.

51
00:06:13.223 --> 00:06:15.392
That's the tragedy of you being blind.
you've never seen me dance.

52
00:06:15.475 --> 00:06:17.477
Yeah. but I can cite the legends
I heard in law school.

53
00:06:17.560 --> 00:06:19.240
So come on. what is it?
What's the problem?

54
00:06:19.312 --> 00:06:22.690
No wingman.
You never come out with me anymore.

55
00:06:22.774 --> 00:06:25.360
Could you imagine
Nelson and Murdock on the dance floor?

56
00:06:25.443 --> 00:06:28.988
I can't deny
that does sound epic.

57
00:06:29.071 --> 00:06:30.365
- Then come out with me. Matt.
- All right.

58
00:06:30.448 --> 00:06:32.367
Come on. just one time. me and you.

59
00:06:33.993 --> 00:06:35.328
What is it?

60
00:06:36.329 --> 00:06:37.455
You're bleeding.

61
00:06:38.206 --> 00:06:41.168
- Huh. Where?
- Base of the skull.

62
00:06:43.170 --> 00:06:45.087
Did you get it?

63
00:06:45.922 --> 00:06:48.466
No one's gonna notice.
if that's what you mean.

64
00:06:48.550 --> 00:06:49.634
Thank you.

65
00:06:50.510 --> 00:06:52.512
- I hate this.
- We don't need to talk about it.

66
00:06:52.595 --> 00:06:54.264
Good thinking.

67
00:06:54.347 --> 00:06:57.392
You know. Karen's been asking questions.
The cuts. the scrapes. the bruises.

68
00:06:57.475 --> 00:06:59.852
- What do you tell her?
- You have a drinking problem.

69
00:07:00.770 --> 00:07:01.938
That's horrible.

70
00:07:02.021 --> 00:07:03.440
Well. it's more plausible than

71
00:07:03.523 --> 00:07:06.067
you put on a devil suit
and beat the shit out of strangers.

72
00:07:06.984 --> 00:07:11.030
You know. this whole thing
isn't just your problem anymore.

73
00:07:11.113 --> 00:07:13.908
And I'm past worrying
about the broken bones.

74
00:07:13.991 --> 00:07:16.161
and finding you beaten into a coma.

75
00:07:17.620 --> 00:07:21.291
- What about us?
- Nelson and Murdock?

76
00:07:21.374 --> 00:07:23.494
You ever stop to think
what happens if you get caught?

77
00:07:23.543 --> 00:07:24.703
At best. you'll be disbarred.

78
00:07:24.752 --> 00:07:27.214
Then you'll continue to do
the good work we started together.

79
00:07:27.297 --> 00:07:28.840
Do you even hear yourself?

80
00:07:29.757 --> 00:07:32.385
You're my partner.
I don't wanna continue alone.

81
00:07:32.469 --> 00:07:33.636
Foggy...

82
00:07:36.055 --> 00:07:39.517
last week. a client came to our office.
Zuly Almeida.

83
00:07:39.601 --> 00:07:41.936
Claimed her life was in danger.
We had no legal recourse to offer.

84
00:07:42.019 --> 00:07:43.646
I remember.

85
00:07:43.730 --> 00:07:46.023
You recommended an excellent shelter
for battered women.

86
00:07:46.107 --> 00:07:48.360
- And she went.
- Yeah. she tried.

87
00:07:49.277 --> 00:07:52.530
That night. her husband found out
she wanted to leave him.

88
00:07:52.614 --> 00:07:53.740
and he followed her to the bus stop

89
00:07:53.823 --> 00:07:56.368
with a gut full of beer
and a butcher knife in his hand.

90
00:07:57.369 --> 00:07:59.489
- You never told me that.
- Well. I'm telling you now.

91
00:08:00.413 --> 00:08:02.290
Mr. Almeida walked out of his apartment

92
00:08:02.374 --> 00:08:06.836
with the intention to hack Mrs. Almeida
into many bloody pieces...

93
00:08:06.919 --> 00:08:08.921
starting by taking off her head.

94
00:08:10.465 --> 00:08:11.758
Guess what?

95
00:08:11.841 --> 00:08:13.009
Never happened.

96
00:08:14.427 --> 00:08:17.222
Instead. he woke up in a hospital
with two broken arms

97
00:08:17.305 --> 00:08:20.267
and a restraining order
safety-pinned to his chest.

98
00:08:20.350 --> 00:08:22.602
Jesus. Matt.

99
00:08:22.685 --> 00:08:25.062
If I take a night off.
people get hurt.

100
00:08:25.146 --> 00:08:27.399
I don't wanna lose you.

101
00:08:27.482 --> 00:08:30.235
- You won't.
- Promise me.

102
00:08:30.318 --> 00:08:33.821
You want me to cross my heart?

103
00:08:34.989 --> 00:08:36.533
Do not make fun of me.

104
00:08:37.825 --> 00:08:39.076
I swear.

105
00:08:40.745 --> 00:08:42.955
Come on. Let's get to work.

106
00:08:43.039 --> 00:08:44.957
Yeah. I gotta get out of this heat.

107
00:08:53.341 --> 00:08:54.717
Idiots.

108
00:08:56.678 --> 00:08:59.389
Good morning. guys.
You take the scenic route this morning?

109
00:08:59.472 --> 00:09:01.724
- Morning to you. too.
- Morning. Karen.

110
00:09:01.808 --> 00:09:03.268
- What have we got?
- All right.

111
00:09:03.351 --> 00:09:07.439
Well. uh. Mr. Marino's dog
was viciously beaten

112
00:09:07.522 --> 00:09:10.442
by his neighbor
after the dog. um...

113
00:09:10.525 --> 00:09:13.653
defiled the neighbor's statue
of Saint Francis.

114
00:09:13.736 --> 00:09:15.071
- "Defiled"?
- Um...

115
00:09:15.154 --> 00:09:17.365
humped repeatedly until completion.

116
00:09:17.449 --> 00:09:21.494
- That's a dog I want to defend.
- Oh. he's... he's all yours. cowboy.

117
00:09:21.578 --> 00:09:24.831
And. uh. Mr. Maxwell here
was attacked in a bar fight last night.

118
00:09:24.914 --> 00:09:25.957
He started it.

119
00:09:26.040 --> 00:09:29.251
Oh. I... I called Metro-General
and the other guy will recover.

120
00:09:29.336 --> 00:09:30.462
but if you are looking at trial.

121
00:09:30.545 --> 00:09:33.298
you probably wanna wait
until his jaw is unwired.

122
00:09:33.381 --> 00:09:35.174
Your girl's a badass.

123
00:09:35.257 --> 00:09:38.511
You've no idea.

124
00:09:39.596 --> 00:09:42.098
Um. and. uh.
Miss Jacinto's working papers

125
00:09:42.181 --> 00:09:44.351
have been denied
for the third time.

126
00:09:44.434 --> 00:09:46.811
Her father's gone
and she says that factory work is

127
00:09:46.894 --> 00:09:48.396
the only way she can support her family.

128
00:09:48.480 --> 00:09:50.231
- Well. tell her not to worry.
- Yeah.

129
00:09:50.315 --> 00:09:52.024
I've already pulled her applications
from the DOE.

130
00:09:52.108 --> 00:09:54.319
Good. because we're gonna find her
something better.

131
00:09:54.402 --> 00:09:56.446
And that's just the appointments
for the first hour.

132
00:09:56.529 --> 00:09:58.448
You wanna talk about our 10:00 a.m.'s?

133
00:10:00.408 --> 00:10:01.534
Uh. what's that?

134
00:10:01.618 --> 00:10:04.036
Oh. uh. the bananas are from Mr. Tate.

135
00:10:04.120 --> 00:10:06.748
Payment for that fender bender thing.
And for you...

136
00:10:06.831 --> 00:10:08.833
Strawberry rhubarb.

137
00:10:08.916 --> 00:10:10.543
You will be mine.

138
00:10:11.794 --> 00:10:13.087
Uh. so. um...

139
00:10:14.213 --> 00:10:17.467
I installed this free trial
of accounting software on my computer.

140
00:10:17.550 --> 00:10:20.428
And the good news is that
I can re-up it every 30 days

141
00:10:20.512 --> 00:10:23.264
with a fake email address. But. um...

142
00:10:24.849 --> 00:10:28.310
the bad news is that...
we're broke.

143
00:10:29.604 --> 00:10:33.232
As in. literally no money.
And our income can't cover our bills.

144
00:10:34.567 --> 00:10:35.943
We'll manage.

145
00:10:36.944 --> 00:10:39.489
I don't know how.
but I know we will.

146
00:10:42.033 --> 00:10:43.535
All right.

147
00:10:43.618 --> 00:10:45.870
Well. in the meantime.
I guess we have. um...

148
00:10:46.996 --> 00:10:49.832
lots of pastries and...
and fruit.

149
00:10:49.916 --> 00:10:51.333
Yeah. and fans.

150
00:10:51.418 --> 00:10:53.044
- Portable. electric fans.
- Yes.

151
00:10:53.711 --> 00:10:56.714
And. uh...
and each other.

152
00:10:58.550 --> 00:11:00.390
Miss Jacinto.
will you come in. please?

153
00:11:02.178 --> 00:11:05.347
Let's see if we can find you a better way
to live in Hell's Kitchen.

154
00:11:05.432 --> 00:11:06.849
Please. sit down.

155
00:11:49.517 --> 00:11:52.687
Apologies. Mr. Nesbitt.
Blood's still up.

156
00:11:53.312 --> 00:11:55.648
Best you mind him. Thomas.

157
00:11:56.983 --> 00:11:58.109
You miserable mutt!

158
00:11:58.192 --> 00:12:00.444
Where was all that fight 10 minutes ago?

159
00:12:18.045 --> 00:12:20.047
Place smells like dog shit!

160
00:12:20.131 --> 00:12:21.841
There's a pot calling the kettle.

161
00:12:26.095 --> 00:12:27.930
Someone get this poor man a drink.

162
00:12:30.182 --> 00:12:34.478
Grotto. you mangy shite.
How's the view up Nesbitt's ass?

163
00:12:40.693 --> 00:12:43.530
Gentlemen. if you'll permit me...

164
00:12:44.614 --> 00:12:46.282
a word before we begin.

165
00:12:48.910 --> 00:12:50.745
This is a night for celebration.

166
00:12:53.998 --> 00:12:56.458
A night to discuss
the future of our family...

167
00:12:58.294 --> 00:13:00.880
the gratitude we feel
for the support of his father.

168
00:13:02.632 --> 00:13:04.884
But perhaps as important...

169
00:13:06.218 --> 00:13:10.472
it is also...
a moment for sober reflection.

170
00:13:10.557 --> 00:13:13.100
Sober. my ass.

171
00:13:19.273 --> 00:13:23.069
Two hundred years ago. our people
were little more than dirt farmers.

172
00:13:23.152 --> 00:13:25.362
struggling just to survive.

173
00:13:25.446 --> 00:13:28.908
They had nothing
but their hopes and their fists.

174
00:13:28.991 --> 00:13:31.744
and they brought both of them along
when they came to America.

175
00:13:31.828 --> 00:13:33.454
many to this very city.

176
00:13:33.537 --> 00:13:35.122
Think you've had enough. George.

177
00:13:39.711 --> 00:13:41.253
Now some of you are young...

178
00:13:41.796 --> 00:13:44.215
so there's no reason you'd remember.

179
00:13:44.298 --> 00:13:50.680
but there was a time
when the Irish owned Hell's Kitchen.

180
00:13:51.848 --> 00:13:55.142
Wasn't a mother's son could
make a move without giving us our due.

181
00:13:55.226 --> 00:14:00.272
and any sorry shite dull enough
to cross us paid a heavy price.

182
00:14:00.356 --> 00:14:03.610
We had the cops. judges. councilmen.

183
00:14:03.693 --> 00:14:06.904
We had the whole bloody city
at our beck and call.

184
00:14:09.406 --> 00:14:11.117
But we got complacent.

185
00:14:11.200 --> 00:14:14.161
Lost our edge.

186
00:14:14.245 --> 00:14:16.956
Just enough for a piece of garbage
like Wilson Fisk

187
00:14:17.039 --> 00:14:19.416
to steal what was rightfully ours.

188
00:14:35.266 --> 00:14:37.184
That's right.

189
00:14:37.268 --> 00:14:38.645
Some of us feared Fisk.

190
00:14:40.104 --> 00:14:41.689
Some. in fact. ran.

191
00:14:42.398 --> 00:14:43.650
A few...

192
00:14:44.609 --> 00:14:46.944
maybe even deigned to work for him.

193
00:14:47.028 --> 00:14:50.031
Siding against their own kind.

194
00:14:56.078 --> 00:14:58.455
But now the Devil's taken him down.

195
00:14:58.539 --> 00:15:02.251
and that. gentlemen. has provided us
with a singular opportunity.

196
00:15:02.334 --> 00:15:03.836
The Russians are dead.

197
00:15:04.754 --> 00:15:06.964
The Chinese. they turned tail and ran.

198
00:15:07.048 --> 00:15:10.342
leaving the drug trade
ripe for the taking.

199
00:15:10.426 --> 00:15:12.178
The yakuza have gone silent.

200
00:15:12.261 --> 00:15:14.806
- Piss on 'em!
- Piss on 'em all!

201
00:15:14.889 --> 00:15:17.599
- Piss on 'em all.
- 'Cause this is our time!

202
00:15:18.851 --> 00:15:20.645
Anyone crosses us.

203
00:15:20.728 --> 00:15:22.772
we'll paint the streets red
with their blood.

204
00:15:22.855 --> 00:15:25.274
And when they're gone.
we'll make your father proud.

205
00:15:25.357 --> 00:15:29.779
and purge ourselves of the filthy traitors
who betrayed their own kind

206
00:15:29.862 --> 00:15:32.824
and make Hell's Kitchen ours again!

207
00:17:36.572 --> 00:17:39.533
See. I don't know. that definitely
sounded like cheating to me. Miss Page.

208
00:17:39.616 --> 00:17:41.660
Foggy. you sure
we're not being hustled here?

209
00:17:41.743 --> 00:17:43.955
As sure as Josie's AC is busted.

210
00:17:44.038 --> 00:17:45.539
What AC?

211
00:17:45.622 --> 00:17:47.083
At least she brought water.

212
00:17:47.166 --> 00:17:48.566
- Oh!
- No. you don't wanna do that.

213
00:17:48.625 --> 00:17:51.212
- You can't drink the water here.
- Josie's pipes have issues.

214
00:17:51.295 --> 00:17:52.922
Rust. mold.

215
00:17:53.005 --> 00:17:55.674
I think I can actually see the bacteria

216
00:17:55.757 --> 00:17:57.077
- floating in there.
- Oh. ew. ew.

217
00:17:58.385 --> 00:18:00.429
See. that... that's why we. uh.
keep our cocktails neat.

218
00:18:00.512 --> 00:18:02.181
Pretend you're abroad.

219
00:18:02.264 --> 00:18:04.308
on vacation someplace exotic.
but no mojitos.

220
00:18:04.391 --> 00:18:05.434
Josie just throws mint in the beer.

221
00:18:05.517 --> 00:18:06.811
- Right.
- Take over. buddy.

222
00:18:06.894 --> 00:18:07.895
I gotta hit the head.

223
00:18:07.979 --> 00:18:10.397
And don't let her out of
your four working senses.

224
00:18:10.481 --> 00:18:12.441
- She's as quick as she is beautiful.
- Right.

225
00:18:12.524 --> 00:18:13.818
She reminds me of myself.

226
00:18:18.364 --> 00:18:21.783
Ah. this place brings out something...
special in Foggy

227
00:18:21.868 --> 00:18:24.245
Are you sure
it's not the alcohol?

228
00:18:24.328 --> 00:18:26.998
No. it's the company.

229
00:18:27.081 --> 00:18:28.624
He likes it when it's the three of us.

230
00:18:30.292 --> 00:18:33.880
If it were up to him. we'd be doing this
the rest of our lives.

231
00:18:37.884 --> 00:18:40.761
God damn it.

232
00:18:40.845 --> 00:18:43.222
- What happened?
- There goes my shutout.

233
00:18:43.305 --> 00:18:45.766
Um. you're going for a shutout
against a blind man?

234
00:18:47.309 --> 00:18:48.644
How do you sleep at night. Miss Page?

235
00:18:48.727 --> 00:18:51.022
You don't get any sympathy
from me. Murdock.

236
00:18:51.105 --> 00:18:53.440
I'm still not sure
who's hustling who here.

237
00:18:53.524 --> 00:18:55.651
All right.

238
00:18:55.734 --> 00:18:56.777
Here's your cue.

239
00:18:58.029 --> 00:19:00.239
All right.
you're lined up with the cue ball.

240
00:19:00.322 --> 00:19:03.284
Six is at your two.
pocket straightaway.

241
00:19:03.367 --> 00:19:05.077
Six and pocket two.

242
00:19:06.578 --> 00:19:07.704
Mmm-hmm.

243
00:19:07.788 --> 00:19:09.373
Fire away.

244
00:19:13.252 --> 00:19:16.172
- How'd I do?
- Well. you've got potential.

245
00:19:16.255 --> 00:19:18.257
- All right.
- Here. go again.

246
00:19:30.561 --> 00:19:32.479
Six ball.

247
00:19:32.563 --> 00:19:34.023
Straight ahead. Just...

248
00:19:35.066 --> 00:19:37.985
real soft.

249
